      <sec id="sec-4-1">
        <title>1 Introduction</title>
        <p>This paper discusses the syntactic alignment of the two major clause types in Old
Japanese (OJ, 8th century): conclusive (1) and what we label ‘nominalized’ clauses,
represented by the adnominal examples in (2).</p>
