    <sec id="sec-10">
      <title>Wokka-e van Wokka-Loc live cho. Perf</title>
      <p>Active alignment can be manifested in the morphological case marked on nouns as
we have seen, but many active languages are strictly head marking: they mark
agreement with NP arguments on the verb. Thus in Guraran´ı a- cross-references SA;
se- cross-references SO:</p>
