    <sec id="sec-12">
      <title>3.2 The nominal hierarchy</title>
      <p>We noted in Sect. 2 that the typological literature has tended to classify active as a
subtype of ergative alignment. One argument against this view is that active
languages differ crucially from ergative languages with respect to how ergative splits
interact with Silverstein’s (1976) nominal hierarchy:
(12)</p>
