        <p>In this section we have presented typological evidence suggesting that both the
alignment and transitive constituent structure properties of OJ nominalized clauses
fit into a larger cross-linguistic pattern. Nominalized clauses may provide the
diachronic source for non-accusative alignment and for a synchronic pattern where the
object appears outside the minimal projection containing the subject and the verb.</p>
