      <p>The word order facts suggest that Japanese was well on the way to developing
accusative alignment even in nominalized clauses by the early EMJ period.
Transitive subjects, regardless of the phonetic form of their case marker, were assigned
case in a position higher than wo-marked objects. This case was spelled out as ga
